race.comment: OAKFIELD WALLABY (3) came with a powerful finish to grab third behind the in-form Meridiana over the mile at Newcastle (metro) last start. Needs this trip now and at the third run back from an extended lay-off should be at her peak. FORMAT (4) defeated subsequent Saturday winner Thebudgiesmugla over 2000m at Hawkesbury two back then floundered on a wet track when stretched to 2400m last time. Big trial winner subsequently. Watch for a return to form. SOSINO (1) led for the judge and was only collared close to home at his latest outing over 1800m at Rosehill. Cherry ripe after four runs back and can win this without surprising. SACRIFY (8) has been going okay south of the border, last time out beaten under three lengths over 2000m at Flemington on Cup Day. This looks a nice race for him. HAPPINESS (7) last raced 44 days ago when third over 2400m at Warwick Farm. Trialled since and should have the residual fitness to be competitive back at this trip.
